{"parentUuid":"81b568df-1aab-486b-9a4b-0d4466c2643a","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/arvos/Tactic/workspaces/workspace-entire-local-cli/entire-local","sessionId":"67920851-1aa5-4602-91b5-bc6bc1ad4386","version":"2.1.69","gitBranch":"master","slug":"reactive-floating-blum","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Improve `subtle` Color for Readability\n\n## Context\nThe `subtle` color variable (`lipgloss.Color(\"241\")`) is too dark on dark terminal backgrounds. It's used for panel borders, stat labels, dim text, inactive tabs, hash styles, help descriptions, tool badges, scroll indicators, and more — all of which are hard to read.\n\n## Change\n\n### `pkg/ui/dashboard/styles.go` — line 11\n\nChange `subtle` from `\"241\"` to `\"245\"`:\n\n```go\nsubtle = lipgloss.Color(\"245\")\n```\n\n`\"241\"` is ~#626262 (very dark gray). `\"245\"` is ~#8a8a8a (medium gray) — readable on dark backgrounds while still clearly secondary to primary content.\n\n### Styles affected (all via the `subtle` variable, no other changes needed)\n- `panelStyle` / `statCardStyle` border color\n- `statLabelStyle`, `hashStyle`, `dimStyle`, `helpDescStyle`, `toolBadgeStyle`, `tabInactiveStyle`, `scrollIndicatorStyle` text color\n\n## Files Modified\n- `pkg/ui/dashboard/styles.go` — one line change\n\n## Verification\n- `make build`\n- Visual: labels, borders, and dim text are noticeably more readable on dark backgrounds\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/arvos/.claude/projects/-Users-arvos-Tactic-workspaces-workspace-entire-local-cli-entire-local/4c9406fa-86be-4466-996c-b32d9393b2fe.jsonl"},"uuid":"d99cd824-84e3-4295-86d2-bdc0c3bbbc4f","timestamp":"2026-03-06T14:26:49.510Z","planContent":"# Plan: Improve `subtle` Color for Readability\n\n## Context\nThe `subtle` color variable (`lipgloss.Color(\"241\")`) is too dark on dark terminal backgrounds. It's used for panel borders, stat labels, dim text, inactive tabs, hash styles, help descriptions, tool badges, scroll indicators, and more — all of which are hard to read.\n\n## Change\n\n### `pkg/ui/dashboard/styles.go` — line 11\n\nChange `subtle` from `\"241\"` to `\"245\"`:\n\n```go\nsubtle = lipgloss.Color(\"245\")\n```\n\n`\"241\"` is ~#626262 (very dark gray). `\"245\"` is ~#8a8a8a (medium gray) — readable on dark backgrounds while still clearly secondary to primary content.\n\n### Styles affected (all via the `subtle` variable, no other changes needed)\n- `panelStyle` / `statCardStyle` border color\n- `statLabelStyle`, `hashStyle`, `dimStyle`, `helpDescStyle`, `toolBadgeStyle`, `tabInactiveStyle`, `scrollIndicatorStyle` text color\n\n## Files Modified\n- `pkg/ui/dashboard/styles.go` — one line change\n\n## Verification\n- `make build`\n- Visual: labels, borders, and dim text are noticeably more readable on dark backgrounds\n"}
